Interview-Friendly Definitions
Question	Answer
What is the Principle of Least Privilege?	Users, applications, and services should have only the minimum permissions needed to perform their tasks.
What is Defense in Depth?	Protecting systems with multiple layers of security so one failed control doesn't compromise the entire system.
Why Minimize the Attack Surface?	Reducing exposed functionality lowers the number of opportunities an attacker has to exploit a system.
What does Fail Securely mean?	When errors occur, systems should default to a secure state rather than granting unintended access.
Why is Security by Default important?	Secure default configurations reduce the chance of vulnerabilities caused by misconfiguration.
